{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"method","extendedModule":"GIO","modules":[{"name":"GIO"}],"title":"close(cancellable:)","externalID":"s:3GIO19InputStreamProtocolPAAE5close11cancellableSbAA14CancellableRefVSg_tKF::SYNTHESIZED::s:3GIO18DataInputStreamRefV","roleHeading":"Instance Method"},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/datainputstreamref\/close(cancellable:)"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"close","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"cancellable"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","text":"CancellableRef"},{"kind":"text","text":"? = nil) "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb"}]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Once the stream is closed, all other operations will return "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"closed"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Closing a stream multiple times will not return an error.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Streams will be automatically closed when the last reference","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"is dropped, but you might want to call this function to make sure","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"resources are released as early as possible."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Some streams might keep the backing store of the stream (e.g. a file descriptor)","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"open after the stream is closed. See the documentation for the individual"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"stream for details."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On failure the first error that happened will be reported, but the close","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operation will finish as much as possible. A stream that failed to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"close will still return "},{"code":"closed","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" for all operations. Still, it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is important to check and report the error to the user."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"cancellable","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is not "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"text":", then the operation can be cancelled by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"triggering the cancellable object from another thread. If the operation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"was cancelled, the error "},{"code":"cancelled","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" will be returned."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Cancelling a close will still leave the stream closed, but some streams"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can use a faster close that doesn’t block to e.g. check errors."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it."}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DataInputStreamRef","doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DataInputStreamRef\/InputStreamProtocol-Implementations"]]},"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DataInputStreamRef\/close(cancellable:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"references":{"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DataInputStreamRef/close(cancellable:)":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/datainputstreamref\/close(cancellable:)","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Closes the stream, releasing resources related to it.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"close"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"cancellable","kind":"externalParam"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:3GIO14CancellableRefV","text":"CancellableRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"throws"},{"text":" -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Bool","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sb","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DataInputStreamRef\/close(cancellable:)","title":"close(cancellable:)"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/InputStream":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStream","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GInputStream"},{"type":"text","text":" is a base class for implementing streaming input."}],"title":"InputStream","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/inputstream","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"InputStream","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"InputStream","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DataInputStreamRef":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/datainputstreamref","title":"DataInputStreamRef","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DataInputStreamRef","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Data input stream implements [class"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/InputStream"},{"type":"text","text":"] and includes functions"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"for reading structured data directly from a binary input stream.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DataInputStreamRef"}],"kind":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"DataInputStreamRef","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/DataInputStreamRef/InputStreamProtocol-Implementations":{"url":"\/documentation\/gio\/datainputstreamref\/inputstreamprotocol-implementations","title":"InputStreamProtocol Implementations","identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DataInputStreamRef\/InputStreamProtocol-Implementations","abstract":[],"kind":"article","role":"collectionGroup","type":"topic"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO":{"type":"topic","abstract":[],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO","title":"GIO","url":"\/documentation\/gio","role":"collection","kind":"symbol"},"doc://GIO/documentation/GIO/CancellableRef":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"CancellableRef","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/CancellableRef","url":"\/documentation\/gio\/cancellableref","abstract":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GCancellable"},{"type":"text","text":" allows operations to be cancelled."}],"title":"CancellableRef"}}}